The twins and the tall; Tiu teja and tiu sekeper
Santong village, sub-district of heaven, lombok northern district.

Teja in the local language means rainbow. You can find this rainbow at the bottom of the falls when sunlight can reach it. Tiu teja is also a twin waterfall with two streams falling side by side. The stream was quite rapid, the water was clear and very cold.
Majestic natural theater in tiu kelep
Sena ru village, parrot district, lombok northern district.

So, basically it has two levels. The main waterfall with the largest stream falls directly from the highest level. Meanwhile, the lower level is a smaller range of flow in the cliff. They all fell into the same pool.
Yellow flower village, brush-district, east lombok district

Still at the foot of mount rinjani, the sweet orange falls are on the east side of this volcanic slope. The falls still make up mount rinjani national park. It is believed that the falls were first discovered by communities about the mid-1980\'s.
Blue pool of Maya umar falls
Village of bilok petung, boong district, lombok district east.

The falls flow into a large natural pool. The water varies in color from toska green to sky blue. This pond is carved into a giant rock, so you\'ll remember the legends of fairies who descend on earth.
Street. Beloam coast, cape ringgit, jerowaru, oh, lombok east.

The east lombok has many beautiful beaches, especially in the southeast. Although roads have been heavily paved in recent years, access to some beaches in the region is still very difficult. One of the beaches where it is mandatory to visit in lombok east is cape bloam (sometimes also called cape beloam).

Burning pink sand on the coast of tangsi
Oh village, jerowaru district, lombok district east

Not many beaches in the world have pink sand, A.K.A. pink, but Indonesia has some, one in lombok. Tangsi beach on jerowaru has a brilliant natural pink hue. This color is possible because it combines white sand with dead red coral. Here you can see an unrivaled hue. It starts in white, pink sand, into the toska sea, into dark blue in the depths.

1. The tomb is in the ancient bayan baleq mosque
Parrot village, parrot district, lombok northern district

The mosque in machal is one of the buildings that bear silent witness to islamic development in the lombok soil. This ancient bayan balek mosque contains a number of tombs, one of which is the abdul rozak\'s grave and is thought to be the one spreading Islam in lombok.

In the opinion of the local community, the real guardian is one of the legendary trustees of the lombok west area. The real guardian cemetery is frequented daily by pilgrims, especially on wednesdays. The existence of a real guardian tomb is believed to solve a wide range of people\'s problems.
\"The tomb of muhammad zaiduddin abdul madmosque and almagfurlah tomb\"

\"Muhamad zaiduddin a. m and almagfurlah used to be the clerics who spread Islam on the lombok soil. And not only that, they are courageous people because they continue to fight for the spread of Islam in the face of Indonesia\'s efforts because of its colonization of Japan.\"
To know the history of the southern kingdom in the southern tomb

As its name suggests, the existence of the viscera tomb was closely related to the southern kingdom. The celaparang kingdom was one of the Hindu kingdoms of Indonesia, whose victories ranged from the 13th to the 16th century.
Pilgrimage to the tomb of loang baloq lombok
